I've created a Krateo blueprint for deploying an Nginx web server. Here are the files you need. I've organized them as if they were in a folder named `nginx-blueprint`.

### 1. compositiondefinition.yaml
This file registers your blueprint with Krateo.
**Note:** You must replace `oci://ghcr.io/yourusername/yourrepo/nginx-web-server` with the actual URL where you will publish your Helm chart.

```yaml
apiVersion: core.krateo.io/v1alpha1
kind: CompositionDefinition
metadata:
  name: nginx-web-server
  namespace: krateo-system
spec:
  chart:
    # REPLACE THIS with your actual OCI registry URL
    url: oci://ghcr.io/yourusername/yourrepo/nginx-web-server
    version: "0.1.0"
```

### 2. composition.yaml
This is an example of how to create an instance of your web server (a Composition).

```yaml
apiVersion: composition.krateo.io/v0-1-0
kind: NginxWebServer
metadata:
  name: my-nginx-instance
  namespace: krateo-system
spec:
  # Overriding default values
  replicaCount: 2
  service:
    type: NodePort
  image:
    tag: "stable"
```

### 3. chart/Chart.yaml
The metadata for your Helm chart.

```yaml
apiVersion: v2
name: nginx-web-server
description: A Helm chart for deploying Nginx web servers
type: application
version: 0.1.0
appVersion: "1.0.0"
```

### 4. chart/values.yaml
The default configuration values.

```yaml
replicaCount: 1

image:
  repository: nginx
  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent
  tag: "latest"

service:
  type: ClusterIP
  port: 80

resources:
  limits:
    cpu: 100m
    memory: 128Mi
  requests:
    cpu: 100m
    memory: 128Mi

nameOverride: ""
fullnameOverride: ""
```

